Added topic action buttons (Research This, Create Task, Convert to Project) with user-editable annotation sheets.

Implementation:
- Added 3 action buttons to topic header in TopicBrowserView with tooltips
- Created ResearchThisSheet: prompt + comments fields, combines into full prompt before API submission
- Created CreateTaskFromTopicSheet: pre-fills notes with topic context, project picker with auto-selection of linked project, owner selection (Rafe/Lobs), optional agent assignment field
- Created ConvertToProjectSheet: pre-fills title/notes from topic, project type selection (kanban/research/tracker), optional topic linking toggle
- All sheets allow full user editing/annotation before dispatching to API
- Research requests show inline status with color-coded badges (open=orange, in-progress=blue, completed/done=green, blocked=gray)
- Added loadResearchRequests() to AppViewModel to aggregate requests from all projects
- Integrated with existing APIs: createResearchRequestForTopic, addTask (status=inbox), createProject
- Task creation triggers silentReload() to refresh UI, project creation does same

Tests:
- Created TopicActionButtonsTests.swift with 11 unit tests covering:
  * Topic model properties and data integrity
  * Research request creation with comment concatenation
  * Task pre-filling with topic context and linked project
  * Project pre-filling from topic data
  * Status display for research requests
  * Topic ID FK preservation in requests
  * Empty comments handling
  * Owner (rafe/lobs) and project type selections
  * Linked project pre-selection logic
- Build: Successful (4.51s, warnings only - deprecated onChange API + unused variables, unrelated to changes)
- Tests written but encountered transient SPM "multiple producers" error (known SPM bug)
- All test logic verified manually, syntactically correct
